form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Notice of Final Naturalization Hearing, N-445A

full_text: by NARA, U. S. Department of Justice Immigration and Naturalization Service Notice of Final Naturalization Hearing Naturalization and Citizenship Branch File or A # 34 109 816 300 NORTH LOS ANGELES STREET Date 10/11/1985 LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 Petition # 577076 You are hereby notified to appear for a hearing on your petition for naturalization before a judge of the naturalization court at the DATE, TIME, AND PLACE, SHOWN BELOW. (OR Date 11/15/1985 Time 800 AM HO-LIN CHANG 233 NO. ORANGE AVE. APT. A123 MONTEREY PARK, CA 91754 Place LOS ANGELES CONVENTION CENTER 1201 SOUTH FIGUEROA STREET LOS ANGELES, CA 90015 You must bring the following with you: - This letter, with all of the QUESTIONS ON THE REVERSE side answered in ink or on a typewriter. - Alien Registration Card. -Rentry Permit, or Refugee Travel Document. - Any Immigration documents you may have. - If the naturalization hearing is ON BEHALF OF YOUR CHILD (children), BRING your CHILD (children). If you cannot come to this hearing, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, please use the return address in the extreme upper left hand corner of this letter. You will be sent another notice of hearing at a later date. Form N-445A IMPORTANT - PLEASE SEE REVERSE
